{{champion:412}}  is very good all around, and is fun to play and even against. 
What's nice is that even though he's good at a lot of different things, some champs will always be better in certain compositions.

Need a sustain support? {{champion:16}} {{champion:37}} {{champion:267}} {{champion:432}} 
Need a tanky support? {{champion:111}} {{champion:89}} {{champion:201}} {{champion:44}} {{champion:12}} 
Need some peel? {{champion:267}} {{champion:201}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:40}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:432}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:25}} 
Need some engage or initiate? {{champion:89}} {{champion:111}} {{champion:53}} {{champion:12}} {{champion:1}} 
Need to boost your ADC or Kog/Varus Mid? {{champion:40}} {{champion:117}} {{champion:26}} 
Need a poke support? {{champion:43}} {{champion:37}} {{champion:143}} {{champion:26}} 

Yes, Thresh is good in a lot of situations, but would you pick {{champion:412}} over {{champion:16}} if you need a dedicated healer? Over {{champion:12}} if you want a supertank who can peel or initiate? Over {{champion:37}} / {{champion:432}} if you want awesome dialogue or lack-thereof? Over {{champion:117}} / {{champion:40}} if you want a Jugger-Maw/Protect-The-Carry comp? Over {{champion:53}} / {{champion:89}} for an initiator? 
Thresh is good. But others are better.
